1.A data type has:
    - name
    - size
    - default value
    8 bit = 1 byte
    - camelCase
    - scope
    - lifetime - how long a variable stays in the memory
    - span - from creation to usage of variable

2. Integer Types:
    - byte - 8bit (-128     127)
    - short - 16bit (-32768     32767)
    - int - 32bit
    - long - 64bit
    - BigInteger
    import java.math.BigInteger;
    BigInteger number = new BigInteger("23847283742389432423");
    System.out.println(number.add(4)); .subtract .multiply .divide .divideAndReminder

    System.out.println(Byte.MIN_VALUE);
    System.out.println(Short.MAX_VALUE);

2. Floating-Point Types:
    - float - 32bit  (precision of 7 digits)
    - double - 64bit (precision of 15-16digits)
    - BigDecimal

3. Conversion:
    - implicit
    - explicit - via cast
    double price = 567.65;
    int count = (int)price

    parse           vs.     cast
    Str -> any              1Num type -> 2Num type

4. Boolean
    boolean hasFridge = false;
    boolean equalA1 = (a == 1)

5. Symbols - %c
    char symbol = 'r';
    System.out.println((int) symbol); -> prints out the ASCII code
    System.out.println((char) 97); -> prints out the symbol

    char firstLetter = 'A';
    char secondLetter = 'B';
    soup(firstLetter + secondLetter) -> 131
    soup("" + firstLetter + secondLetter) -> 131

6. String
    .length()
    .charAt()
    .toLowerCase()
    .toUpperCase()
    .equals()

SHIFT + F6 -> rename the variable in all occurences
